comments.content:
Another first post today, welcome Wesley!   
   
I thought it was T26's Aaux, but I checked the website and it doesn't match. We'll keep looking!   
   
On a side note, I was just telling another fellow searcher that when you post on the type ID section, it helps if you give the thread a more descriptive name. Otherwise, particular searches get difficult to locate among the many threads.   
   
Good luck with this one.

alrite, no problem   
bare with me this was my first post...   
 ![:-)](http://web.archive.org/web/20081121161458im_/http:/www.typophile.com/forums/clipart/happy.gif)

no need to apologize, we are here to help ![:-)](http://web.archive.org/web/20081121161458im_/http:/www.typophile.com/forums/clipart/happy.gif)   
   
still no match for that face, though ![:-(](http://web.archive.org/web/20081121161458im_/http:/www.typophile.com/forums/clipart/sad.gif)

Yay! Tom nails it. ![:-)](http://web.archive.org/web/20081121161458im_/http:/www.typophile.com/forums/clipart/happy.gif)   
   
These guys from [Definingform](http://web.archive.org/web/20081121161458/http:/www.typophile.com/forums/messages/83/40545.html?1089843615) sure are big fans of [Acmefonts](http://web.archive.org/web/20081121161458/http:/www.identifont.com/show?4N8).   
First [Klampenborg](http://web.archive.org/web/20081121161458/http:/www.typophile.com/forums/messages/83/40544.html?1089745387), now this one...

I knew I had seen this one before, what I didn't remember is that [I asked for it](http://web.archive.org/web/20081121161458/http:/www.typophile.com/forums/messages/83/10831.html) before...   
   
Ah, shame!
